LendingPlatformManages the overall functionality of the lending platform. Interacts with othercontracts and coordinates lending, borrowing,interest calculations, and user interactions.Stores global parameters such as interest rates, collateralization ratios, and platform settings.TokenContractsSeparate contracts for each supported token (e.g., ERC-20 tokens like DAI, USDC, ETH). Handles token transfers, balances, and allowances.Provides functions for depositing, withdrawing, and transferring tokens.LendingPoolManages the pool of deposited tokens andtracks user balances and accrued interest.Receives deposits from lenders and lends out tokens to borrowers.Calculates and updates interest rates and distributes interest payments to lenders.BorrowingContractHandles borrowing activities, including collateral locking, loan issuance, and repayment.Validates loan requests, collateral ratios, and liquidation conditions.Liquidates collateral if borrowers default on their loans.InterestRateModelCalculates dynamic interest rates based onsupply and demand dynamics.Determines interest rates for lenders and borrowersbased on market conditions and platform parameters. Provides functions for querying current interest rates and updating rate models.Oracle ContractRetrieves external market data such as token prices, exchange rates, and asset values. Used for calculating collateral values, determining liquidation thresholds, and updating interest rates based on market conditions.Access ControlImplements access control mechanisms to manage permissions and roles within the platform. Ensures that only authorized users can perform specific actions such aslending, borrowing, or updating contract parameters.yTokenIt represents users' shares in the lending pool and offers functionalities such as minting/burning tokens, interest accrual, transferability, redemption, integration with the lending platform, and optional governance rights. These tokens enable users to participate in lending, borrowing, and other DeFi activities while earning interest on their deposited assets.
